53    /**
54    * DisambiguateProperties renames properties to disambiguate between unrelated
55    * fields with the same name. Two properties are considered related if they
56    * share a definition on their prototype chains, or if they are potentially
57    * referenced together via union types.
58    *
59    * <p> Renamimg only occurs if there are two or more distinct properties with
60    * the same name.
61    *
62    * <p> This pass allows other passes, such as inlining and code removal to take
63    * advantage of type information implicitly.
64    *
65    * <pre>
66    * Foo.a;
67    * Bar.a;
68    * </pre>
69    *
70    * <p> will become
71    *
72    * <pre>
73    * Foo.a$Foo;
74    * Bar.a$Bar;
75    * </pre>
76    *
77    */
